“If you look at it keenly, we really need BBI,” Kimani shot, fearlessly. Why? I thought.
“BBI is nothing but a boring storybook that is being forced on everyone including non-readers. It’s poorly written fiction, if you may” Wajohi retorted. This was getting interesting.
Yes and No camps
“The two of you sound like a “Yes and No teams” already. I think it’s a good place to start the discourse. I will be the IEBC. Let’s go,” I joked.
“Look,” Kimani continued, “It all depends on how you look at it. With a bloated parliament, you stand a chance to be a Mheshimiwa. It is also necessary that you consider most of these people who are supporting BBI are old enough to retire from politics when BBI is passed. Now imagine Mheshimiwa Wajohi?” Kimani argued.



