“That argument does not hold water,” Wajohi could not take any of Kimani’s explanation. “You should be initiated in the Kenyan political scene to understand that in Africa, age does not matter. Look at Museveni, how old is the champ? Do you know Bobi Wine was four years when Museveni, now his embittered political rival, took power? That case alone should be enough to convince you that old age in Africa is not synonymous to retiring from politics,” Wajohi picked his metallic cup filled with hot supu from the butcher’s table and gulped.



