“I still maintain that you have to look at the bright side of this document. Don’t focus too much on the shortcomings,” Kimani added, to Wanjohi’s irritation.
“I must add that when the youth ask for jobs from the government, and they are asked to create their own jobs, it is the Kenyan version of Marie Antoinette, who, when asked for bread, told the French to eat cake,” Wajohi finished the discussion with a reflection.



