As the referee, I must say, it was difficult to determine who had won the debate. But of importance was not winning or losing. It was understanding that whether BBI is good and should be adapted, or it is bad and should be discarded, depends largely on the gaze through which one views it. If you look at it from an elitist and bourgeoisie eye, it’s the right document. But if you look at it from the eyes of walala hoi, you’ll despise it. Should the majority decide?
   If the BBI Amendment Bill passes, the youth will be assured of at least two seats at the National Assembly. The handshake has transformed DP William Ruto to an opposition leader in his own government. He served in former president Daniel Moi's cabinet. BBI secretariat cleaned up the 5.2 million signatures that endorsed the Bill, and weeded out 800,000 that had entry irregularities. This comes days after he collapsed at a hotel in Nairobi and was placed under intensive care at Nairobi Hospital.